Date: Thu, 13 Nov 2025 11:12:34 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] BFD Config not applied to vtysh in unified mode

Issue: When "docker_routing_config_mode" is configured in "unified"
mode, the BFD_PEER table is read from config_db.json by frrcfgd and
corresponding bfd commands are supposed to be executed in vtysh. This is
failing.

RCA: When we manually push the BFD_PEER via redis-cli, it works because
data expected is a plain string, and it receives the same.
data[param] == 'up'

However, when we add the same in config_db.json, we receive the data as
follows:
data[param] == (up, ADD)

The above is handled properly for scenarios like bgp_af_handler, but was
missed for bfd.

Fix: Updated the code to handle the above problem.

Signed-off-by: sarabjeets <sarabjeets@marvell.com>
---
 .../frrcfgd/frrcfgd.py                        | 91 +++++++++++--------
 1 file changed, 53 insertions(+), 38 deletions(-)

